PORT ELIZABETH - The Eastern Cape has confirmed its first COVID-19 case. Premier Oscar Mabuyane has called for calm and vigilance. READ: South Africa's COVID-19 cases rise to 240 Eastern Cape Health MEC Sindiswa Gomba said about four people were exposed to the woman who was diagnosed with COVID-19 after travelling to Germany. The contacts traced after her trip are being monitored for symptoms. Her partner who also travelled to the European country had no symptoms following the trip. Gomba said testing teams have been made available for large metropolitans in the province and the teams have now been extended to district hospitals. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.